Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.32,0:23:55.57,ED01 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}{\fad(0,480)}Futari arukidasu
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.94,0:00:07.48,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,One human only has the power to do so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.33,0:00:25.83,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm going to protect...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.83,0:00:28.42,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...even if it's just a handful of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.21,0:00:31.30,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...the ones most important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.93,0:00:37.68,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,A subordinate protects their subordinate, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.93,0:00:41.35,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That should be possible, even for us puny humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.35,0:00:42.68,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Geometric progression?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.44,0:00:45.56,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Which means this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.44,0:00:48.86,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to protect this whole country,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.86,0:00:51.53,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,you have to be at the top of the summit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.94,0:00:57.36,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It must feel great up there, Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.49,0:01:02.54,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't climb to the top with my own strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.50,0:01:05.29,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.29,0:01:07.67,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting all worked up for?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.54,0:01:11.17,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.17,0:01:13.13,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.13,0:01:17.72,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see what kind of changes\Nyour naive ideals will bring to this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.97,0:01:24.68,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.56,0:01:26.44,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.98,0:01:31.86,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,Why not head to the nap room if you're tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.86,0:01:34.23,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.86,0:01:39.62,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to finish up the documents I've started before I get transferred to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.16,0:01:42.41,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't slept much lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.41,0:01:44.62,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed you were dreaming about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.75,0:01:48.71,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What? Just a boring flashback.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:25.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember anything after being kicked by this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:31.69,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,"Guardians with only souls",\N"precious sacrifices", "being kept alive".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.27,0:03:36.27,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,"Tattoo of Ouroboros", and\N"transmutation circle for a philosopher's stone".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.27,0:03:40.19,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,According to Dr. Marcoh,\Nthe stones were used in Ishbal, as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.86,0:03:44.36,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,There are too many mysteries for it to be an ordinary experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.36,0:03:49.41,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to look into it some more,\Nbut the research lab is in ruins now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.41,0:03:51.41,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.50,0:03:56.04,Default,Brosh,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like they're discussing something tricky...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.04,0:04:00.46,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like getting involved in something dangerous again, so I refuse to listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:02.22,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.09,0:04:07.14,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the Fullmetal Alchemist's recovery room?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.14,0:04:08.68,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he's in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.27,0:04:15.23,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,We may be able to discover something if we look through the court-martial chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:22.19,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go and investigate the ones who were participating in the research of the stones under Dr. Marcoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:27.24,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to intrude.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.37,0:04:34.33,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,F-Führer-President... King Bradley!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.33,0:04:37.38,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet down. You can be at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.88,0:04:40.50,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Your Excellency, may I ask why you are here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.75,0:04:42.17,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Why I'm here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.71,0:04:43.92,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,To visit this boy, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.92,0:04:45.59,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Are you fond of melon at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:47.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.72,0:04:48.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, something's wrong here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:54.60,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like you've been doing a lot of investigating of the military leadership, Major Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.60,0:04:57.65,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! Well... that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.65,0:04:59.19,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,How did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.19,0:05:01.40,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate my intelligence network.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:05.65,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Edward Elric...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:08.49,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,The philosopher's stone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:14.37,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Just how much did you find out?\NDepending on that, I may have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.55,0:05:25.51,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.13,0:05:27.93,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,No need to get tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:29.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:34.39,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, was aware there have been\Ndisquieting activities within the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.39,0:05:37.35,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted to do something about them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:39.27,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.27,0:05:42.73,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,A list of people who were researching the philosopher's stones, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.40,0:05:47.03,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Every one of them has been reported missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:47.61,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:51.87,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,They have been reported missing a few days prior to the destruction of Research Laboratory 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:54.79,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy is always ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:05:59.58,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Even with my intelligence network,\Nwe still don't know the scale of it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:04.38,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,their objectives, or how close they are to achieving them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.21,0:06:09.05,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying it's extremely dangerous for us to look into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:10.18,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.59,0:06:12.01,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.01,0:06:13.93,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Major Armstrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.93,0:06:15.60,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Elric Brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:19.02,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided you all are trustworthy people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:24.78,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I forbid you to continue investigating this matter or to disclose it to others!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:31.03,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot trust anyone in a situation like this,\Nwhen you cannot even distinguish friend from foe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.16,0:06:36.04,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Regard all of the military as your foe and proceed carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.45,0:06:37.54,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:42.46,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,When the time comes, I will have many tasks for all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.46,0:06:43.63,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,So be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.63,0:06:44.71,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.42,0:06:46.51,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Your Excellency!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.51,0:06:48.67,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you gone, Your Excellency?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:52.26,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, drats! Here comes my annoying subordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.68,0:06:57.27,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I snuck out of my office, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.77,0:06:59.23,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:05.98,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.98,0:07:06.57,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.86,0:07:09.90,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.90,0:07:13.49,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just say... a storm just went by.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.03,0:07:18.62,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I went out and bought the tickets you asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.62,0:07:20.75,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow's afternoon train, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.04,0:07:23.08,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.08,0:07:27.55,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you in such a rush?\NYour wounds haven't even healed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.55,0:07:31.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stay in a place reeking of antiseptics like this forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.84,0:07:33.51,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.26,0:07:35.14,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Dublith?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:36.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.85,0:07:41.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,After discussing it with Al, we decided to stop by our master's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.15,0:07:44.90,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared, Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.27,0:07:47.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're probably going to get killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.98,0:07:49.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,C-Courage, my little brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.86,0:07:51.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just as scared as you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:54.16,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person is your master...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.70,0:07:58.29,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Dublith is quite far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:07:59.58,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:03.33,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... It's here. It's right in the middle of the South.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:09.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:12.84,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,This place! Before Dublith!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.18,0:08:17.05,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,The Holy Land of Automails, Rush Valley!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:18.85,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted to go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.01,0:08:20.47,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Please take me! Please take me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.47,0:08:22.27,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Take me! You better take me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.27,0:08:24.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.10,0:08:26.35,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Who's going to pay for the trip, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.35,0:08:28.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're planning on making {\i1}me{\i0\fscx30} {\r} pay for it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.06,0:08:30.61,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, why not? It's on the way, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.19,0:08:32.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.69,0:08:34.24,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:37.99,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to give Granny a call!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.91,0:08:43.37,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she'll make a grand wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:44.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell {\i1}me{\i0\fscx30} {\r} that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:48.25,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Not as grand as my wife, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.63,0:08:52.17,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Papa's going to be on his way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.17,0:08:55.30,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to come home early today, Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:57.76,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.76,0:08:59.80,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Papa's got a lot of work to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.10,0:09:02.81,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll come home as soon as I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:06.69,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.19,0:09:10.86,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to be leaving today, right, Winry?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.86,0:09:13.03,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see you off because of work, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:14.49,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.57,0:09:18.91,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm truly indebted to you, Mr. Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.66,0:09:23.20,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to drop by if you ever come to Central again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.75,0:09:25.62,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.62,0:09:28.38,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,And give my regards to those boys, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.38,0:09:29.04,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.04,0:09:31.50,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck at work, Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.50,0:09:32.92,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:46.60,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you decide to go visit your master all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:09:48.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Two reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.85,0:09:51.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,First off, we've kind of been on a losing streak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.86,0:09:52.77,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.77,0:09:54.82,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're going because you want to get stronger?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:56.19,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys, muscleheads?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.70,0:10:00.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! It's not that simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.03,0:10:03.74,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We don't just want to get stronger physically, but should we say mentally, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:04.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.62,0:10:06.00,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.00,0:10:10.08,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we feel like we'll be able to get stronger if we visit our master.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.75,0:10:13.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I want to become far stronger than I am now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.84,0:10:17.72,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And your second reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:21.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I want to ask about philosopher's stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:25.18,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The real truth that is beyond truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:27.93,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We never found out the meaning of those words, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.93,0:10:30.73,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Our master might know something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:33.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We can't be caring about how we're going to look out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.48,0:10:37.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to ask our master while being prepared to be killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.57,0:10:39.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.53,0:10:41.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.62,0:10:45.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It was a short-lived life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.33,0:10:48.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could have had a girlfriend, at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.71,0:10:50.87,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person is your master?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.50,0:10:54.00,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,A riot in Lior?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:10:54.92,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.34,0:11:01.59,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the riot caused by some Leto cult\Ndeceiving the citizens has finally calmed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.09,0:11:02.89,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.68,0:11:07.02,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,With Ishbal and other riots...\Nthe East sure have their hands full.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:12.48,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Not just the East, but there are riots and border wars\Nsparking up in the North and the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:15.94,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Mountains of corpses everywhere, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.94,0:11:18.15,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,We may even get a coup soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.24,0:11:26.62,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you headed, Lt. Colonel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:28.33,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,To the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.63,0:11:36.42,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Riots throughout Lior.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.09,0:11:40.13,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,The ingredients of philosopher's stones are humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:43.64,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What we did in Ishbal...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:50.02,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa now, who's the mastermind behind all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.02,0:11:52.31,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I've got to hurry and let the Führer-President know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.40,0:11:58.48,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.48,0:12:02.65,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Or should I say... farewell?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.96,0:12:18.63,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Cool tattoo you've got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.21,0:12:22.05,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,You found out too much, Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.69,0:12:39.82,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.91,0:12:49.78,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,That's something {\i1}I{\i0\fscx30} {\r} should be saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.08,0:12:54.87,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.87,0:12:57.25,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here to call someone about your family again-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:12:59.00,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel, you're bleeding!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:02.09,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. I need to use the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.42,0:13:05.18,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I need to call the Führer-President building...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.97,0:13:15.23,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to bother you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.77,0:13:16.64,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:19.48,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? You've reached Eastern Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.48,0:13:22.40,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Let me talk to Roy... Colonel Roy Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.69,0:13:25.49,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,We're not permitted to relay direct calls from an outside line.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:27.57,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Lt. Colonel Hughes from Central!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.57,0:13:29.45,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling from a phone booth because of an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.45,0:13:30.70,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,Please give me the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:32.74,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What a bother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.91,0:13:38.88,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle-Sugar-Oliver-Eight-Zero-Zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.00,0:13:41.38,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,I've verified the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.38,0:13:42.84,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,One moment, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.84,0:13:44.09,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.09,0:13:45.34,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,The military is in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.85,0:13:53.81,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,Could you put down the receiver, Lt. Colonel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.81,0:13:57.56,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,The receiver, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.73,0:14:01.90,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,2nd Lt. Ross... or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.90,0:14:02.94,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.86,0:14:06.82,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,I'm 2nd Lt. Maria Ross. Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.82,0:14:07.95,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.03,0:14:12.95,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,2nd Lt. Ross has a mole under her left eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:16.20,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.20,0:14:18.08,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,I was careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:22.09,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,How's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.80,0:14:25.34,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.34,0:14:27.34,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if I'm dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.72,0:14:32.72,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Your quick-wittedness brought the end of you, Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:35.10,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.56,0:14:38.14,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a wife and a daughter waiting for me at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.14,0:14:39.98,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:42.11,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,...I can die here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.53,0:14:46.94,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect staging, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:49.65,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.75,0:15:01.17,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes from Central is on a public line.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.17,0:15:02.46,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:03.84,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Put him through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.84,0:15:05.04,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.04,0:15:06.38,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If it's about your daughter again, I'm hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.22,0:15:10.76,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hughes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.97,0:15:13.26,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hughes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.26,0:15:14.60,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hughes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.19,0:15:24.94,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are so foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.94,0:15:27.36,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Risking their lives for something so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.12,0:15:38.33,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Elicia... Gracia...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.04,0:15:40.16,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.04,0:15:45.88,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I can... keep my promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.09,0:15:54.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.35,0:15:57.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,These apple pies are awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.64,0:16:01.02,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Gracia is such a good cook!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.02,0:16:02.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.44,0:16:05.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The quiche she made for us once was really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.81,0:16:10.94,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's on my "list of things to eat when I get my body back".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.94,0:16:15.32,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,She taught me how to make it, so I'll bake one for you when you get your body back, Al.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:16.91,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.33,0:16:21.79,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hughes and Miss Gracia are both wonderful people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:27.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes is such a doting father...\Nand kind of annoying because he's so meddlesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.79,0:16:31.30,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He always came to poke fun at you in your hospital room, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.51,0:16:32.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:40.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's always saying he's busy with work, yet he paid me a visit every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:42.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We have to thank him next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:44.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.88,0:17:20.35,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Mama... why are they burying Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:22.85,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,Elicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.85,0:17:26.94,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Papa won't be able to go to work if they do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:28.48,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,Elici...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.36,0:17:33.78,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Papa said he had a lot of work to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.86,0:17:36.03,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.45,0:17:38.24,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bury him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.87,0:17:40.37,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.79,0:17:46.21,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Specially promoted two ranks after being killed in the line of duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:48.37,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Brigadier General Hughes... huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.83,0:17:53.09,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were going to work under me and support me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.63,0:17:55.01,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point if you surpass my rank?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.55,0:17:57.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.22,0:17:58.89,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:07.27,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists are unpleasant creatures, aren't they, Lieutenant?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.52,0:18:14.53,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm desperately putting together the theory of human transmutation in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.78,0:18:21.16,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I know how those boys felt when they tried to transmute their mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:25.66,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.54,0:18:28.54,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.04,0:18:32.54,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it looks like it's beginning to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.96,0:18:36.38,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:41.30,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's raining all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:45.47,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.18,0:18:47.27,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.73,0:18:49.56,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,We'll catch colds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.27,0:18:54.61,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,He left the room saying that\Nhe was going to go to the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.36,0:18:58.11,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,That was the last I saw of the Lt. Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.40,0:19:02.45,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Did he fight with someone in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:03.74,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.24,0:19:07.87,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,There were bloodstains from the room to the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.75,0:19:10.79,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,And his next destination was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.00,0:19:15.92,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel tried to make a phone call,\Neven while he was injured...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.92,0:19:20.42,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,But... he left without doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:25.97,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,He realized something in the court-martial chamber...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.97,0:19:31.69,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...and took the trouble to contact me from the outside when he could have called from within the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.73,0:19:37.69,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The telephone operator in the Eastern Headquarters heard Hughes say, "The military is in danger".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.90,0:19:39.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.53,0:19:42.53,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What was he trying to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:49.50,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel, I've brought Major Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.54,0:19:57.38,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We have an idea of the ones who murdered Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.38,0:19:59.34,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't you take them into custody?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:03.72,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We have an idea, but we don't know exactly who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:07.72,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? Tell me in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:09.72,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:13.06,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I, a Colonel, am telling you to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.06,0:20:14.60,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to disobey a senior officer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.61,0:20:16.61,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.99,0:20:23.24,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.24,0:20:25.07,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for calling you out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.07,0:20:26.20,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You may go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.20,0:20:27.07,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.37,0:20:34.87,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, I forgot to mention.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.87,0:20:38.75,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,The Elric Brothers had been staying here until a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:41.01,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The Elric Brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.01,0:20:43.38,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Elric Brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.51,0:20:47.76,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Did they find what they were looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.93,0:20:48.97,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.97,0:20:52.27,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What they are looking for is almost legendary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.98,0:20:55.14,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:00.86,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't get much out of him, could we?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.86,0:21:02.65,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.65,0:21:04.36,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The Major is truly good-natured.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:08.24,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,He said specifically,\N"ones who murdered Lt. Colonel Hughes".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.24,0:21:11.12,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there were several.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:14.16,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It could be that they're working as an organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.41,0:21:19.38,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If he can't speak, even under order from a colonel,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.38,0:21:24.55,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,that means someone higher ranked than me is imposing silence on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.17,0:21:27.55,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,We can assume the top of the military is behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.51,0:21:31.56,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,And the thing the Elric Brothers are looking for...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.35,0:21:34.43,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the philosopher's stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.06,0:21:41.61,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,An organization that has a hand in the military leadership, the philosopher's stone, and Lt. Colonel Hughes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.61,0:21:43.48,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Just how does it all relate...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.48,0:21:45.07,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,As for now, we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.86,0:21:53.20,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But once I get transferred to Central, I'll investigate the leadership and find out who killed Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.70,0:21:56.79,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It's unlike you to mix up private and public matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.79,0:21:58.83,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,There are no "private" or "public" matters involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.83,0:22:03.17,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Aiming to become Führer-President and avenging Hughes' death...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.67,0:22:05.59,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...are both my will as an individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.55,0:22:09.09,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Our target will be the military leadership. You're coming with me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.97,0:22:11.35,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'll back down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.58,0:24:05.21,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al run through Rush Valley, chasing after Paninya, a girl who stole Ed's silver pocket watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.50,0:24:10.55,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,although they have no idea what's awaiting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.76,0:24:16.26,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.26,0:24:20.27,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 11, Miracle at Rush Valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.73,0:24:24.19,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,The words the boy engraved were words of resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.40,0:24:25.44,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Or could they be...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
